    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Articles of Agreement between <persName role="author">Isaac Leeser</persName> of the
                one part<lb/> and the Portuguese Jewish Congregation of the City of
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> incorporated by the name, style and
                title of <add>ק"ק מקוה ישראל</add> Kohel Radosh<lb/> Mikveh Israel of the other part
                made and entered into at the City of <placeName>Phi<lb/>ladelphia</placeName> on the
                    <date>twenty second day of the month of Kislev in the year 5598</date>,
                corresponding<lb/> with the <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> day of December
                    1837</date> as follows to wit.</p>
            <p>First. The said <persName role="author">Isaac</persName> covenants on his part to
                officiate and serve as <add>חזן</add> or Reader<lb/> to the said congregation for at
                least one year from the <date>first day of the Jewish month Tishry</date><lb/> last
                part, corresponding with the <date>thirtieth day of September 1837</date> now last
                past, and<lb/> for so much longer of a period of two years, being a period of three
                years for which<lb/> he has been elected, in case the difference of salary
                    <del>of</del> now in dispute between<lb/> him and the congregation be properly
                adjusted, during which continuance in office<lb/> he will faithfully
                    <sic>fulfil</sic> the duties usually incident to said station, that he will on
                every <date>Sabbath</date><lb/> eve, morning and night, and on all the holy days
                &amp; festivals, and such other times<lb/> when the Synagogue is open for worship
                attend at the Synagogue and then &amp; there<lb/> in a devout manner read the
                prayers in the original Hebrew language,<lb/> according to the custom of the
                Portuguese Jews; that he will attend the funerals<lb/> (under proper limitation)
                that take place in the burial ground of the congregation<lb/> and perform the
                funeral and subsequent mourning service; that he will not<lb/> at any time perform
                any marriage or funeral rites without the consent<lb/> of the Parnass or of the
                Adjunta; that he will support and abide by the<lb/> Charter and Bylaws of the
                congregation; and that he will obey the orders of<lb/> the Parnass or
                    Segan<add>?</add> in the Synagogue with regard to calling up and<lb/>
                distribution of the Mitzvote, and never absent himself for more than<lb/> twenty
                four hours without the knowledge and consent of the Parnass, or in<lb/> his absence
                the senior Adjunta.</p>
            <p>Second: In consideration of the said services the said congregation agrees<lb/> to
                pay him the sum of eight hundred Dollars pr annum unless otherwise ordered<lb/> by a
                meeting of the congregation, in quarterly payments of two hundred each<lb/> or in an
                increased proportionate sum on the <date>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of March</date>,
                        <date>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of June</date><lb/>
                <date>29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of September</date> and <date>29<hi rend="sup"
                        >th</hi> of December</date> in each and every year, or when lawfully</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>thereafter demanded by said <persName role="author">Isaac</persName>
                <add>?</add> for the due and faithful performance<lb/> of the foregoing covenant
                each party do the hereby bind himself unto the other<lb/> in the penal sum of one
                thousand Dollars.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In witness whereof the said <persName role="author">Isaac
                    Leeser</persName> hath hereunto set his<lb/> hand &amp; seal, and the said Kabal
                Kadosh Mikveh Israel have hereunto<lb/> caused their common corporate seal to be
                affixed attached by their<lb/> Parnass and Secretary, the day and year first
                hereinbefore written</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">Isaac Leeser</persName>
            </p>
